                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. FRITH</hi>. I should not be surprised to hear that Bangham was at Chatham; he might come up and down frequently, Chat<lb></lb>ham is very close to Waterloo Bridge, about an hour's ride—I was first asked to give evidence here about three weeks ago, and I went to Newgate to see the prisoners—I did not go to the Treasury and make a statement—they did not ask me—a detective came to me to inquire about the prisoners never had my evidence taken down in writing.</p>
